n</i>.  See  Mowe   (1) and  compare  Mawson  . Some of the following earlier bearers may alternatively belong with (2).","2  English: post-medieval variant of   Mawson   (2), with the vowel rounded to give  <i>Mowson</i>.","3  English: post-medieval variant of   Molson   (  see  Moulson  ), if not vice versa."]},{"name":"Moston","meanings":["1  English: locative name from Moston (Lancs), Moston by Chester or Moston Green (both Cheshire), or Moston in Stanton upon Hine Heath (Shrops). There has probably been some confusion with (2).","2  Welsh, English:  see  Mostyn  ."]},{"name":"Mossom","meanings":["1  English: (i) variant of   Mawson  , as suggested by John Mawson, 1723, Wm. Mosson, 1745 in   IGI  , Isabella Mossom, 1758 in   IGI   (Auckland Saint Andrew, Durham). (ii) alternatively, a variant of   Mowson  , or   Molson   (  see  Moulson  ). Compare Alice Mowson, 1663 in   IGI   (Durham, Durham) and Richardi Mowson, 1586 in   IGI   (Wrawby, Lincs), but in Durham  <i>Mowson</i> could also be a variant form of (1) and in Lincs  <i>Mosson</i> and  <i>Mossom</i> may alternatively belong with (2).","2  English: perhaps a variant of   Motson  ."]},{"name":"IGI","meanings":["English: perhaps an altered form of   Pritchett   or   Pritchard  . Compare Katherine Pratchett, 1654, Janam Pritchett, 1675 in   IGI   (Acton by Nantwich, Cheshire); Gulielmus Pritchard, 1675, Mary Pratchett, 1698 in   IGI   (Hatfield, Herts)."]},{"name":"Mawson","meanings":["English:","patronymic from   Maw   1.","metronymic from a form of   Maude   2."]}]},{"name":"Thomas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Thomas Mosson was born in 1409, in Hoghton, Lancashire, England as the son of Emma Smith. He had at least 1 daughter with Sarah De Bothe. He died in 1429, in Lancashire, England, at the age of 20."},"et":{"1409–1429":"1409–1429","1412–1470":"1412–1470","1429–1468":"1429–1468","1397–1408":"1397–1408","1468":"1468","1412":"1412","after 1408":"pärast 1408","1397":"1397","1409":"1409","1470":"1470","1408":"1408","1429":"1429","Hoghton, Lancashire, England":"Hoghton, Lancashire, England","Lancashire, England":"Lancashire, England"},"fi":{"1409–1429":"1409–1429","1412–1470":"1412–1470","1429–1468":"1429–1468","1397–1408":"1397–1408","1468":"1468","1412":"1412","after 1408":"1408 jälkeen","1397":"1397","1409":"1409","1470":"1470","1408":"1408","1429":"1429","Hoghton, Lancashire, England":"Hoghton, Lancashire, England","Lancashire, England":"Lancashire, England"},"fr":{"1409–1429":"1409–1429","1412–1470":"1412–1470","1429–1468":"1429–1468","1397–1408":"1397–1408","1468":"1468","1412":"1412","after 1408":"après 1408","1397":"1397","1409":"1409","1470":"1470","1408":"1408","1429":"1429","Hoghton, Lancashire, England":"Hoghton, Lancashire, Angleterre","Lancashire, England":"Lancashire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Thomas Mosson est né en 1409, à Hoghton, Lancashire, Angleterre, fils d’Emma Smith. Il a eu au moins 1 fille avec Sarah De Bothe. Il est décédé en 1429, à Lancashire, Angleterre, à l’âge de 20 ans."},"de":{"1409–1429":"1409–1429","1412–1470":"1412–1470","1429–1468":"1429–1468","1397–1408":"1397–1408","1468":"1468","1412":"1412","after 1408":"nach 1408","1397":"1397","1409":"1409","1470":"1470","1408":"1408","1429":"1429","Hoghton, Lancashire, England":"Hoghton, Lancashire, England","Lancashire, England":"Lancashire, England","lifeSummary":"Thomas Mosson wurde 1409 in Hoghton, Lancashire, England, als Sohn von Emma Smith geboren. Er hatte mit Sarah De Bothe mindestens 1 